  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/critical-theory/domains/marxism/domains/political-economy/terms/pareto-condition/> ;
  schema:name "Pareto Condition" ;
  schema:description "The Pareto condition (or Pareto optimality) is a criterion from welfare economics: a state of affairs is Pareto optimal if no one can be made better off without making someone else worse off. A change is a Pareto improvement if it benefits at least one person while harming no one." ;
